The paper focuses on reinforcement learning in cooperative multiagent systems, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of generative adversarial imitation learning (GAIL) and self-imitation learning also suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a Sub-Curriculum Experience Replay mechanism, which could be related to robotics (cs.RO) and multiagent systems (cs.MA).
